<@U026AP8CM>, is there a harvest for this sequencing stuff?
<@U026PLK4S>: let me set something up.
I have something set up for maintenance, but let's keep this separate for now, since we anticipate we'll run this as a separate project.
<@U026AP8CM> and <@U026103R3>  it looks like Susan has messed up the BFF apple developer account.
oh lovely
she made the primary email to be her email (apple id is <mailto:nicole@miany.com|nicole@miany.com>)
I "resent" her a validation email
I hope all she needs to do is validate it.
should i send her a note with a heads up
yes
please - it is blocking my ability to create a build
so you can't log in with nicoles email?
no
gotcha
it gets you in but apple is gating me
with a screen about managing the apple ID
oh susan
she did it but never verified it, so now apple has effective locked it until she verifies it.
i see
I could switch it back nicole
it gives me that option
would that let you back in?
or would nicole need to verify then?
I think/hope so - without verifying.
ok, i say go for it. <@U026AP8CM> agrees
if it needs to then be verified by nicole we can just explain and send a note to both of them
let us know what happens
ok
<@U026PLK4S>: "sequencing" is now a project under BFF.
thanks
nope...  that did nothing.

<@U026AP8CM> - can you email BOTH nicole and susan and ask them to check they email addresses for an apple email asking them to verify.   at the moment I really need nicole to do it on the <mailto:nicole@miany.com|nicole@miany.com> address
And <@U026AP8CM> - If I am submitting the build by EOD, you need to get everything setup in iTunes Connect
yes
understood, thanks <@U0289USNA>!
<@U026AP8CM>: i am pretty busy but i can help/answer questions on getting itunes connect set up
ok
<@U0289USNA>: just sent susan & nicole an email.
will follow up once I hear anything.
hey also - we'll need copy for the iOS update in english and spanish
any time we push an update we need that "what's new" copy
it's part of getting itunes set up
:simple_smile:    What's new? - Restoring Push Notifications.
en Español - Restauración de Notificaciones Push
<@U0289USNA>: nicole says it's done.
thanks
she wants to know if we can remove this email address?
<@U0289USNA>: susan's asking if she needs to click verify as well? she received an email in addition to nicole.
I am good right now - but I have likely undone whatever Susan was attempting to do in terms of adding her email to the account
did she just add one of the vroom ones with zeros as O's?
<@U0261PCRQ>: <@U0289USNA> just a friendly reminder to log your time for push notifications under maintenance quarter 1 listed under BFF.

 - Scott Bates
i got a push notification!! wahoo
It's not on your correct time slot at the moment, but regardless, yes you got a push notification!
woo!
better than nothin
how important is it that the custom sound play on android devices?
<@U026103R3>? I apologize, I don't know how important this is.
what's the back story on the question
i think it's pretty important
#missionCritical
there's no built in way to add sound to android notifications
I was using all local content previously
and now that we're using data from the server, I don't want to overwrite it
so what are our options
we can use local notifications like we were doing before
and users won't see the dynamic content
sorry - what dynamic content? aren't we still just saying "your vroom is ready"
yes
but if they ever want to send different content, then we would have to update the app, otherwise it will keep saying "your vroom is ready"
don't worry about them ever wanting dynamic pushes
they don't, i've asked a bunch of times
even if they did, we could cross that bridge when we got to it and explain the caveats
and update the app
so let's keep it local and have the custom sound
ok
thank youuu
